      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "ISF's strength lies in its niche focus on 'upstream' influence. By awarding over <cite id=\"13\">$3,060,000 in total funds</cite> since inception, they have built a pipeline of Muslim professionals in fields that shape public opinion. Their governance is marked by <cite id=\"14\">100% independent board members</cite>, and they have successfully met <cite id=\"15\">all 20 BBB Wise Giving Alliance Standards</cite> for charity accountability."
      ],
      "summary": "The Islamic Scholarship Fund (ISF) is a specialized non-profit organization dedicated to <cite id=\"1\">increasing American Muslim representation</cite> in public policy, media, and legal fields. Founded in <cite id=\"2\">2009</cite>, the organization addresses the underrepresentation of Muslim voices in the American narrative by providing <cite id=\"3\">scholarships, film grants, and congressional fellowships</cite>. ISF operates with a high degree of transparency, evidenced by its <cite id=\"4\">Platinum Seal from Candid</cite> and an <cite id=\"5\">overall score of 91.91.66666666666667/100 from Charity Navigator</cite>. Financially, the organization reported <cite id=\"6\">total revenue of $1,014,133</cite> in its most recent filing, maintaining a <cite id=\"7\">program expense ratio of 65.0%</cite>. Beyond financial aid, ISF focuses on career trajectory, reporting that <cite id=\"8\">88% of its alumni are working in their field of study</cite> and maintaining a <cite id=\"9\">100% graduation rate</cite> among its scholarship recipients. The organization also facilitates direct civic engagement through <cite id=\"10\">Congressional Policy Internships and Judicial Internships</cite>, bridging the gap between academic achievement and professional influence in the public sector.",
